<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long does a plastic surgery consultation typically last?</h3>
<p>Most consultations last between 30 minutes and one hour, depending on the complexity of your concerns and the number of procedures being discussed. Dr. Johar ensures that every consultation is thorough and that all your questions are answered before you leave.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Should I bring anything to my consultation?</h3>
<p>It is helpful to bring a list of your questions, reference photos that illustrate your goals, a complete list of current medications, and your medical records if you have had recent tests or treatments. Having this information ready makes the consultation more productive.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Will I be charged for the initial consultation?</h3>
<p>Consultation fees vary by clinic. At Dr. Johar's clinic, the consultation fee is designed to reflect the comprehensive evaluation and personalized guidance you receive. Contact the clinic for current pricing information and any available fee credits toward your procedure.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I get a second opinion after my consultation?</h3>
<p>Absolutely. Seeking a second opinion is a common and wise practice when considering plastic surgery. A reputable surgeon will never discourage you from getting additional perspectives. The goal is for you to feel fully confident in your decision.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What if I am not a good candidate for the procedure I want?</h3>
<p>If the surgeon determines that a particular procedure is not the best fit for you, they will explain why and recommend alternative options that may be more suitable. Patient safety always comes first, and a good surgeon will never perform a procedure that poses an unnecessary risk.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How many consultations should I have before deciding on surgery?</h3>
<p>There is no set number of consultations required. Some patients feel confident after a single consultation, while others prefer to meet with multiple surgeons before deciding. Taking the time you need to feel comfortable and informed is always encouraged.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What happens if I change my mind after booking surgery?</h3>
<p>You can cancel or reschedule your surgery at any time before the procedure. Most clinics have cancellation policies that are outlined during the booking process. Your decision to proceed should always feel voluntary and well-considered.</p>
</div>
</div>

